 Work on breaking LCG's includes:

 Boyar, J.  1989.  Inferring Sequences Produced by Pseudo-Random
 Number Generators.  Journal of the ACM.  36(1): 129-141.  (Has
 a good bibliography.)

 Also see:

 Hastad, J. and A. Shamir.  1985.  The Cryptographic Security of
 Truncated Linearly Related Variables.  Proceedings of the 17th
 ACM Symposium on Theory of Computing.  356-362.

 which builds upon and generalizes:

 Frieze, A., R. Kannan and J. Lagarias.  1984.  Linear Congruential
 Generators do Not Produce Random Sequences.  Proceedings of the
 25th IEEE Symposium on the Foundations of Computer Science.
 480-484.  (This is [2] of Stern.)

